1
00:00:01,840 --> 00:00:03,000
(LAUGHING)

2
00:00:03,080 --> 00:00:04,720
I told you it'd work.

3
00:00:04,840 --> 00:00:06,240
It very nearly ate you for dinner.

4
00:00:06,320 --> 00:00:08,280
Oh, admit it. I totally saved your life.

5
00:00:09,040 --> 00:00:10,280
It wasn't going to eat me.

6
00:00:10,360 --> 00:00:11,440
(LAUGHS)

7
00:00:11,520 --> 00:00:15,920
I totally saved you from having to marry
that giant sentient plant thing.

8
00:00:16,440 --> 00:00:19,240
That bit, when I jumped
over the side, that was amazing.

9
00:00:20,160 --> 00:00:21,320
-(CHUCKLES)
-(LAUGHS)

10
00:00:21,400 --> 00:00:22,600
Knew you were impressed.

11
00:00:22,680 --> 00:00:25,400
The second most beautiful
garden in all of time and space

12
00:00:25,480 --> 00:00:28,440
and we can never come back here,
because you, Miss Oswald, decided...

13
00:00:28,520 --> 00:00:29,840
(PHONE RINGING)

14
00:00:34,200 --> 00:00:35,960
(RINGING CONTINUES)

15
00:00:47,960 --> 00:00:49,760
-Hello.
-RIGSY: Clara, finally.

16
00:00:49,840 --> 00:00:50,960
It's Rigsy.

17
00:00:51,040 --> 00:00:52,720
Oh, Rigsy!

18
00:00:52,800 --> 00:00:53,800
Hey. What's wrong?

19
00:00:54,480 --> 00:00:56,080
So, I have this, uh...

20
00:00:57,120 --> 00:00:58,520
It kind of looks like a tattoo.

21
00:01:01,760 --> 00:01:04,360
CLARA: Seriously, I gave you
this number for emergencies.

22
00:01:04,440 --> 00:01:05,720
It's an emergency. Trust me.

23
00:01:06,160 --> 00:01:08,840
Just, come and take
a look at it, please.

24
00:01:09,680 --> 00:01:11,200
Who said you could give out my number?

25
00:01:11,280 --> 00:01:12,280
Look, look.

26
00:01:12,360 --> 00:01:13,600
No matter how bad it is

27
00:01:13,680 --> 00:01:16,480
we cannot take you
back down your timeline

28
00:01:16,560 --> 00:01:17,800
just to fix a tattoo.

29
00:01:18,640 --> 00:01:19,840
That's just it.

30
00:01:19,920 --> 00:01:21,480
I didn't get a tattoo, and it's...

31
00:01:22,280 --> 00:01:23,400
It's counting down.

32
00:01:24,600 --> 00:01:25,680
Sorry. What?

33
00:01:26,040 --> 00:01:27,040
The tattoo.

34
00:01:27,360 --> 00:01:29,200
It's a number
and it's counting down to zero.

35
00:01:29,600 --> 00:01:30,840
Hang tight. We'll be right there.

36
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:33,160
Hurry. Please.

37
00:01:38,920 --> 00:01:40,920
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

38
00:02:16,240 --> 00:02:17,840
(WHOOSHING)

39
00:02:19,080 --> 00:02:20,320
DOCTOR: Did you make this human?

40
00:02:20,400 --> 00:02:22,000
Lucy? Yeah, she's mine.

41
00:02:22,080 --> 00:02:23,080
CLARA: Oh!

42
00:02:23,960 --> 00:02:25,080
Hello.

43
00:02:25,160 --> 00:02:27,440
Oh, Rigsy, she's gorgeous.

44
00:02:27,960 --> 00:02:29,200
DOCTOR: She's better than that.

45
00:02:29,920 --> 00:02:31,120
She's brilliant.

46
00:02:31,640 --> 00:02:33,040
What are you doing running around
getting tattoo...

47
00:02:33,120 --> 00:02:34,120
(BOTH SHUSHING)

48
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:38,320
(SOFTLY) Look, I didn't get anything.

49
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:40,240
I woke up this morning
and it was just there.

50
00:02:40,320 --> 00:02:41,320
Jen noticed it.

51
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:43,160
Okay. Show me this tattoo
that you didn't get, then.

52
00:02:45,200 --> 00:02:46,640
(LUCY COOS)

53
00:02:48,000 --> 00:02:49,720
It's a tattoo. It's very boring.

54
00:02:49,800 --> 00:02:52,000
No, wait. Look.
Just... Just keep watching.

55
00:02:52,080 --> 00:02:53,400
What were you doing last night?

56
00:02:53,880 --> 00:02:55,200
That's just it.

57
00:02:55,280 --> 00:02:56,760
Yesterday was a total blank.

58
00:02:57,720 --> 00:03:00,240
Jen said that I left
the house before dawn.

59
00:03:00,320 --> 00:03:01,640
I missed work.

60
00:03:01,720 --> 00:03:03,480
And I didn't get back
till after midnight.

61
00:03:03,560 --> 00:03:05,120
No one saw me all day.

62
00:03:07,560 --> 00:03:09,200
Oh, that's not boring.

63
00:03:10,920 --> 00:03:13,600
That is very not boring.

64
00:03:15,560 --> 00:03:16,760
-(WHIRRING)
-What? What is it?

65
00:03:18,280 --> 00:03:19,280
Okay, local knowledge.

66
00:03:20,440 --> 00:03:22,240
You're coming with us,
and bring the new human.

67
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:25,640
No. Don't bring the new human.
I'll just get distracted.

68
00:03:30,600 --> 00:03:32,640
DOCTOR: If you want
your extremities to stay attached,

69
00:03:32,720 --> 00:03:34,040
stand absolutely still.

70
00:03:34,120 --> 00:03:35,920
If not, we can provide a small bag.

71
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:37,200
You can take them home at the end.

72
00:03:38,880 --> 00:03:40,200
CLARA: Rigsy, your phone.

73
00:03:41,600 --> 00:03:44,040
It's like they've wiped it,
but only the last day.

74
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:46,960
No location data, no texts, nothing.

75
00:03:48,720 --> 00:03:50,760
You sure the screen
wasn't cracked before yesterday?

76
00:03:50,880 --> 00:03:51,880
Uh-huh.

77
00:03:52,760 --> 00:03:54,520
Oh, right. Okay, here we go.

78
00:03:54,600 --> 00:03:55,680
Uh...

79
00:03:56,160 --> 00:03:57,200
Good.

80
00:03:57,480 --> 00:03:58,520
Weird.

81
00:03:58,600 --> 00:03:59,600
Good and weird.

82
00:03:59,800 --> 00:04:00,920
(MUMBLING) Can I move?

83
00:04:01,680 --> 00:04:03,400
Ah. Oh, yes, yes, yes, yes. Of course.

84
00:04:05,800 --> 00:04:07,040
First off,

85
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:10,440
in the last 24 hours you have
had significant contact

86
00:04:10,520 --> 00:04:12,200
with alien life forms.

87
00:04:12,280 --> 00:04:13,880
Right here, in the centre of London.

88
00:04:13,960 --> 00:04:16,200
Okay, so, why don't I remember anything?

89
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:18,240
You've been Retconned.

90
00:04:18,320 --> 00:04:19,360
-RIGSY: Huh?
-What conned?

91
00:04:19,760 --> 00:04:21,280
Amnesia drug.

92
00:04:21,360 --> 00:04:24,000
Your prefrontal cortex
is marinating in it.

93
00:04:24,320 --> 00:04:25,680
(COMPUTER BEEPING)

94
00:04:25,760 --> 00:04:27,640
Ooh, there's something else.

95
00:04:28,240 --> 00:04:29,240
Something...

96
00:04:30,240 --> 00:04:31,840
(ALARM SOUNDING)

97
00:04:33,080 --> 00:04:34,280
DOCTOR: Uh...

98
00:04:34,760 --> 00:04:35,960
Not good.

99
00:04:37,120 --> 00:04:38,120
Weird.

100
00:04:53,200 --> 00:04:54,240
RIGSY: What's he doing?

101
00:04:56,560 --> 00:04:58,120
He's making an effort to be nice.

102
00:04:58,720 --> 00:05:01,760
There's no nice way
to say you're about to die.

103
00:05:01,880 --> 00:05:02,880
What?

104
00:05:08,560 --> 00:05:09,760
-Rigsy...
-No, no, no, no, no!

105
00:05:09,840 --> 00:05:11,640
Don't start using my actual name now.

106
00:05:11,720 --> 00:05:14,240
Call me pudding brain. Call me
local knowledge, whatever. Just...

107
00:05:14,320 --> 00:05:15,320
Don't call me Rigsy.

108
00:05:16,960 --> 00:05:18,320
You're gonna save me.

109
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:20,080
You're a Doctor. That's what you do.

110
00:05:21,280 --> 00:05:22,280
(SIGHS)

111
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:32,240
(SMACKS LIPS) Okay, okay.

112
00:05:33,120 --> 00:05:34,200
Yes!

113
00:05:34,280 --> 00:05:35,920
Okay, let's do this thing.

114
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:38,000
First up, stop the countdown.

115
00:05:38,080 --> 00:05:40,040
526 minutes. Right!

116
00:05:40,120 --> 00:05:41,240
Okay.

117
00:05:41,320 --> 00:05:42,520
Yes. You know what?

118
00:05:42,600 --> 00:05:43,600
Local knowledge,

119
00:05:43,680 --> 00:05:46,400
I don't know who did this to you or why.

120
00:05:46,480 --> 00:05:48,560
But I do almost certainly know...

121
00:05:48,640 --> 00:05:49,760
(TARDIS POWERING UP)

122
00:05:49,840 --> 00:05:50,880
How to find them.

123
00:05:53,200 --> 00:05:54,560
(WHOOSHING)

124
00:05:57,200 --> 00:05:58,680
(SIREN WAILING)

125
00:06:00,120 --> 00:06:01,200
There have always been rumours.

126
00:06:01,280 --> 00:06:03,400
Stories passed
from traveller to traveller,

127
00:06:03,480 --> 00:06:06,000
mutterings about hidden streets.

128
00:06:06,080 --> 00:06:10,120
Secret pockets of alien life
right here on Earth.

129
00:06:10,320 --> 00:06:11,760
Like a smuggler's cove.

130
00:06:12,240 --> 00:06:13,240
Only not a cove,

131
00:06:13,320 --> 00:06:15,560
because it's right here,
right in the middle of the capital.

132
00:06:15,640 --> 00:06:17,440
The hidden places are in
the great British Library?

133
00:06:17,520 --> 00:06:19,240
No. The maps are.

134
00:06:21,720 --> 00:06:23,120
DOCTOR: I never put stock in it.

135
00:06:23,200 --> 00:06:26,280
London streets that suddenly
disappear from human view. No.

136
00:06:26,360 --> 00:06:28,480
You lot are always overlooking things.

137
00:06:28,560 --> 00:06:31,560
But whole streets,
that would be excessive even for you.

138
00:06:31,960 --> 00:06:34,240
But if the stories are true, though,

139
00:06:34,320 --> 00:06:36,160
there should be a street
in one of these old maps

140
00:06:36,240 --> 00:06:37,760
that no longer exists in the real world.

141
00:06:38,200 --> 00:06:40,400
Like a trap street, only not.

142
00:06:41,440 --> 00:06:43,280
-What did you say?
-A trap street.

143
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:45,440
You know, when someone's making a map.

144
00:06:45,520 --> 00:06:47,240
A, um, cartographer.

145
00:06:47,320 --> 00:06:49,160
Uses a fake street,
throws it into the mix,

146
00:06:49,240 --> 00:06:51,320
names it after
one of his kids or whatever.

147
00:06:51,400 --> 00:06:53,360
Then if the fake street,
the trap street,

148
00:06:53,440 --> 00:06:54,800
ever shows up on someone else's map,

149
00:06:54,880 --> 00:06:56,280
they know their work's been stolen.

150
00:06:56,360 --> 00:06:57,360
Clever, right?

151
00:06:57,760 --> 00:06:59,880
My God! A whole London street
just up and disappeared

152
00:06:59,960 --> 00:07:02,200
and you lot assume
it's a copyright infringement.

153
00:07:02,280 --> 00:07:04,160
So, we're looking for a trap street?

154
00:07:04,440 --> 00:07:05,880
We're looking for a trap street.

155
00:07:05,960 --> 00:07:07,200
And we're not going to find it here.

156
00:07:07,720 --> 00:07:10,040
The glasses are tracking
your eye movements.

157
00:07:10,120 --> 00:07:12,000
Just keep looking straight down...

158
00:07:12,080 --> 00:07:13,520
I know!

159
00:07:13,600 --> 00:07:16,360
Focus on the buildings
directly below me!

160
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:19,360
DOCTOR: Whatever they're using,

161
00:07:19,440 --> 00:07:21,600
it only hides the street itself.

162
00:07:21,960 --> 00:07:25,000
It prevents you from noticing there's
even something missing.

163
00:07:25,600 --> 00:07:28,000
They'll somehow make
our eyes skate right over it.

164
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:30,320
It's called a misdirection circuit.

165
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:31,800
(EXCLAIMS)

166
00:07:32,960 --> 00:07:34,280
(CLARA EXCLAIMS)

167
00:07:35,040 --> 00:07:36,080
(CLARA SCREAMS)

168
00:07:36,160 --> 00:07:37,160
Clara!

169
00:07:37,240 --> 00:07:39,640
CLARA: Whoo-hoo! (LAUGHS) Whoo!

170
00:07:39,720 --> 00:07:42,320
Whoo-hoo! (LAUGHING)

171
00:07:42,400 --> 00:07:43,840
Whoo!

172
00:07:43,920 --> 00:07:45,960
(YELLS) Hello, London!

173
00:07:46,200 --> 00:07:47,200
(CLARA LAUGHS)

174
00:07:47,320 --> 00:07:48,440
(CLARA EXCLAIMS)

175
00:07:48,600 --> 00:07:49,600
(CLARA LAUGHS)

176
00:07:51,160 --> 00:07:52,200
CLARA: Phew!

177
00:07:52,360 --> 00:07:53,440
(CLARA LAUGHS)

178
00:07:54,760 --> 00:07:56,000
I'm good.

179
00:07:56,080 --> 00:07:57,080
(LAUGHS)

180
00:07:58,320 --> 00:07:59,440
CLARA: I'm good.

181
00:07:59,600 --> 00:08:02,240
She enjoyed that way too much.

182
00:08:02,760 --> 00:08:03,920
Tell me about it.

183
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:05,400
It's an ongoing problem. Here.

184
00:08:06,320 --> 00:08:08,040
(GRUNTS) Keep it steady.

185
00:08:09,720 --> 00:08:11,640
Just move it slowly over the grid.

186
00:08:12,280 --> 00:08:13,560
When we're done
we'll have a map of the areas

187
00:08:13,640 --> 00:08:15,120
of the grid that Clara
couldn't focus on.

188
00:08:18,040 --> 00:08:20,360
So these are the bits
my eyes skated over.

189
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:23,000
DOCTOR: Okay, we split up.

190
00:08:23,080 --> 00:08:24,320
Clara, that way.

191
00:08:25,080 --> 00:08:26,320
Local knowledge.

192
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:31,280
DOCTOR: Forget the way
you usually look at the world.

193
00:08:31,360 --> 00:08:33,600
This street's going to be
hiding in plain sight.

194
00:08:33,680 --> 00:08:34,840
Twenty-two, 23...

195
00:08:34,920 --> 00:08:38,240
DOCTOR: If you see something
unusual or notable, dismiss it.

196
00:08:38,320 --> 00:08:39,520
Just keep walking.

197
00:08:41,040 --> 00:08:43,400
But if there's a bit of London
so unremarkable

198
00:08:43,480 --> 00:08:45,120
that you don't even think about it,

199
00:08:46,280 --> 00:08:47,280
stop.

200
00:08:47,680 --> 00:08:50,960
You could very well
be standing right outside a trap street.

201
00:08:51,040 --> 00:08:53,080
Count everything that you see.

202
00:08:53,160 --> 00:08:55,160
Four, five, six...

203
00:08:55,240 --> 00:08:57,760
Because when you hit
the area around a trap street,

204
00:08:57,840 --> 00:09:00,200
it's very likely you'll lose count.

205
00:09:02,120 --> 00:09:03,400
Seventy-nine.

206
00:09:04,040 --> 00:09:05,040
Eighty.

207
00:09:05,840 --> 00:09:06,840
Eighty-one.

208
00:09:08,320 --> 00:09:09,320
Eighty-two.

209
00:09:09,880 --> 00:09:12,120
-Huh?
-Remember 82.

210
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:13,760
-WOMAN: Come along.
-Eighty-two.

211
00:09:16,120 --> 00:09:19,080
DOCTOR: You'll lose count
because the misdirection circuit

212
00:09:19,160 --> 00:09:21,880
Is creating confusion in your mind.

213
00:09:21,960 --> 00:09:23,680
Details won't add up.

214
00:09:23,760 --> 00:09:26,040
Reality will have glitches in it.

215
00:09:26,720 --> 00:09:29,960
Like when you try to read the same
simple sentence three times over...

216
00:09:30,040 --> 00:09:31,480
One, two, three...

217
00:09:31,560 --> 00:09:33,920
DOCTOR: ...and the meaning
Just won't sink in.

218
00:09:37,920 --> 00:09:38,960
Got ya.

219
00:09:45,520 --> 00:09:46,880
DOCTOR: Clara. Clara.

220
00:09:47,760 --> 00:09:48,760
Clara.

221
00:09:52,040 --> 00:09:53,720
It's off this street, I am certain.

222
00:09:53,800 --> 00:09:55,000
We're very close.

223
00:09:55,960 --> 00:09:57,760
We need to distract our other senses.

224
00:09:57,840 --> 00:09:59,120
Clara, go back to the Tardis.

225
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:00,920
Pick up all my most annoying stuff.

226
00:10:02,720 --> 00:10:04,240
(BEEPING)

227
00:10:04,320 --> 00:10:05,320
(GROANS)

228
00:10:05,400 --> 00:10:06,400
(PANTS)

229
00:10:06,480 --> 00:10:07,760
(MOBILE BEEPING)

230
00:10:18,640 --> 00:10:19,840
What happened to all
the stuff that I asked...

231
00:10:19,920 --> 00:10:21,120
Someone called you.

232
00:10:21,200 --> 00:10:23,160
Yesterday, 6:00 a.m. Blocked number.

233
00:10:23,240 --> 00:10:24,240
Oh.

234
00:10:29,040 --> 00:10:30,080
(GASPING)

235
00:10:32,560 --> 00:10:33,560
(SNIFFS)

236
00:10:34,040 --> 00:10:35,600
She's dead. (GROWLS)

237
00:10:36,640 --> 00:10:37,640
What is it?

238
00:10:38,640 --> 00:10:40,120
What are you remembering?

239
00:10:41,200 --> 00:10:42,480
(GASPING)

240
00:10:45,360 --> 00:10:47,320
Rigsy, what is it?

241
00:10:50,040 --> 00:10:51,360
You can't see it?

242
00:10:51,440 --> 00:10:52,440
There.

243
00:11:07,840 --> 00:11:09,360
I see it. You?

244
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:12,640
Fifty minutes left.

245
00:11:13,640 --> 00:11:15,920
Hoodie up, local knowledge.

246
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:17,560
They know what you look like in there.

247
00:11:29,480 --> 00:11:31,560
RIGSY: How come I saw it
when you guys couldn't?

248
00:11:31,640 --> 00:11:33,400
Well, you were upset, weren't you?

249
00:11:33,480 --> 00:11:35,800
Something slipped through
the Retcon memory.

250
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:38,040
Something that
took over your whole mind.

251
00:11:38,120 --> 00:11:40,200
Something juicy.

252
00:11:40,760 --> 00:11:43,880
So the misdirection circuit,
it lost its power over you.

253
00:11:44,320 --> 00:11:46,840
Surely people wander
in here all the time then, distracted,

254
00:11:46,920 --> 00:11:48,200
on their phones or whatever.

255
00:11:48,600 --> 00:11:49,480
Well, perhaps they do.

256
00:11:49,560 --> 00:11:50,640
Oh!

257
00:11:52,600 --> 00:11:54,120
(ALARM SOUNDING)

258
00:11:59,760 --> 00:12:00,760
(SNARLS)

259
00:12:08,320 --> 00:12:09,720
Flee at once!

260
00:12:10,520 --> 00:12:11,520
It's you!

261
00:12:14,080 --> 00:12:15,200
Hang about.

262
00:12:15,280 --> 00:12:16,360
(SNIFFS)

263
00:12:16,440 --> 00:12:18,240
Uh, this one don't smell human.

264
00:12:19,520 --> 00:12:21,880
Name, species, and case for asylum.
Quick as you like.

265
00:12:22,760 --> 00:12:24,200
-Asylum?
-The reason you're here.

266
00:12:24,280 --> 00:12:25,640
The reason you need sanctuary.

267
00:12:28,680 --> 00:12:30,080
Why didn't they use the protocol?

268
00:12:30,160 --> 00:12:31,560
I saw through the circuit again.

269
00:12:31,640 --> 00:12:33,320
I saw them.
They're definitely not human.

270
00:12:34,960 --> 00:12:37,080
You do know this is a refugee camp.

271
00:12:38,720 --> 00:12:39,840
(CHUCKLES)

272
00:12:40,120 --> 00:12:41,560
Yeah, of course.

273
00:12:41,640 --> 00:12:42,640
ASHILDR: Of course he does.

274
00:12:43,840 --> 00:12:45,040
Now that you've told him.

275
00:12:45,120 --> 00:12:46,320
Mayor Me.

276
00:12:48,160 --> 00:12:49,160
CLARA: Ashildr.

277
00:12:49,480 --> 00:12:50,480
Ashildr?

278
00:12:51,360 --> 00:12:53,000
That's your name.

279
00:12:53,080 --> 00:12:54,280
I keep telling you that.

280
00:12:54,640 --> 00:12:55,640
Do you?

281
00:12:56,360 --> 00:12:58,400
Infinite lifespan, finite memory,

282
00:12:58,480 --> 00:13:00,440
it makes for an awkward social life.

283
00:13:01,240 --> 00:13:03,560
You must be Clara Oswald.

284
00:13:03,640 --> 00:13:05,480
You're as beautiful as your photos.

285
00:13:06,880 --> 00:13:08,160
We met.

286
00:13:08,240 --> 00:13:10,280
Yes, I know. It's in my diaries.

287
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:13,640
Oh, don't look like that.
I enjoyed our conversations.

288
00:13:13,720 --> 00:13:15,320
I've read them many times.

289
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:18,320
Okay, that's slightly odd but nice.

290
00:13:18,920 --> 00:13:21,240
Um, hang on.
So this is where you've been.

291
00:13:21,320 --> 00:13:23,080
That's why he lost track of you.

292
00:13:24,080 --> 00:13:25,720
Oh, come on, please.

293
00:13:26,200 --> 00:13:28,040
It's really cute.
He thinks I don't know.

294
00:13:28,120 --> 00:13:29,560
He's got this whole
secret room in the Tardis

295
00:13:29,640 --> 00:13:30,720
where he collects mentions of you.

296
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:32,160
It's not cute.

297
00:13:34,520 --> 00:13:35,720
It's surveillance.

298
00:13:35,800 --> 00:13:36,960
It's professional interest.

299
00:13:37,040 --> 00:13:38,320
Precautionary measure.

300
00:13:38,880 --> 00:13:40,040
Still saving the world from me then?

301
00:13:40,120 --> 00:13:41,440
It's still here, isn't it?

302
00:13:42,720 --> 00:13:43,840
CLARA: He lost track of you,

303
00:13:44,400 --> 00:13:46,640
in the early 1800s.
I wondered if you were...

304
00:13:46,720 --> 00:13:48,840
Oh, no. I let him know I was okay.

305
00:13:51,880 --> 00:13:53,280
I saw you. (CHUCKLES)

306
00:13:53,480 --> 00:13:55,360
No. I got your attention.

307
00:13:55,480 --> 00:13:57,160
Yes, you did and you have.

308
00:13:57,680 --> 00:13:58,680
Now we need your help.

309
00:13:58,760 --> 00:14:02,880
Someone in this place
is in control of a quantum shade.

310
00:14:07,400 --> 00:14:08,400
(GROWLS)

311
00:14:09,640 --> 00:14:11,840
RUMP: I knew I recognised that smell.

312
00:14:12,160 --> 00:14:14,000
-Oh!
-Ashildr.

313
00:14:14,080 --> 00:14:15,080
What's going on?

314
00:14:27,400 --> 00:14:28,400
You.

315
00:14:28,880 --> 00:14:30,880
How do you know this man?

316
00:14:31,280 --> 00:14:33,240
Hang on. You did this to Rigsy?

317
00:14:34,640 --> 00:14:35,680
What have you done?

318
00:14:36,080 --> 00:14:38,720
This man committed a crime.

319
00:14:41,040 --> 00:14:42,920
-ASHILDR: I sentenced him.
-Sentenced him?

320
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:46,720
I also gave him enough time to return
home and say goodbye to his family.

321
00:14:46,800 --> 00:14:48,480
You flooded his brain with Retcon.

322
00:14:48,560 --> 00:14:51,040
Till we showed up, he didn't even know
that he had to say goodbye.

323
00:14:51,120 --> 00:14:54,240
I'm afraid no intruder
leaves this place without a memory wipe.

324
00:14:54,320 --> 00:14:56,560
With respect, that will include you.

325
00:14:56,640 --> 00:14:58,000
Oh, the hell it will.

326
00:14:58,080 --> 00:15:02,040
Ashildr, given that we're all gonna
forget this conversation anyway,

327
00:15:02,120 --> 00:15:04,080
perhaps you could tell us
what happened here yesterday

328
00:15:04,160 --> 00:15:06,120
to necessitate a death sentence.

329
00:15:07,560 --> 00:15:08,560
Fine.

330
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:10,360
I'll show you.

331
00:15:11,880 --> 00:15:14,360
Mr Kabel, Mr Rump,

332
00:15:14,440 --> 00:15:15,440
permit them entry.

333
00:15:15,720 --> 00:15:16,720
No.

334
00:15:17,760 --> 00:15:19,600
You've already endangered
one of my friends.

335
00:15:20,280 --> 00:15:21,960
I want your personal guarantee

336
00:15:22,040 --> 00:15:23,880
that you will not endanger another.

337
00:15:24,520 --> 00:15:26,000
Shut up. I can handle myself.

338
00:15:27,440 --> 00:15:30,120
I guarantee the safety of Clara Oswald.

339
00:15:30,200 --> 00:15:33,280
She will be under
my personal protection.

340
00:15:33,360 --> 00:15:34,560
That is absolute.

341
00:15:34,880 --> 00:15:36,440
If that's your wish, Mayor Me.

342
00:15:41,480 --> 00:15:42,560
ASHILDR: This way.

343
00:15:43,640 --> 00:15:44,680
Murderer.

344
00:15:45,760 --> 00:15:46,760
What did you say?

345
00:15:47,880 --> 00:15:49,080
(WHIRRING)

346
00:15:54,800 --> 00:15:56,080
Murderer.

347
00:15:57,840 --> 00:15:59,480
He called me a murderer.

348
00:16:04,960 --> 00:16:07,040
DOCTOR: So, you're still
calling yourself "Me" then?

349
00:16:07,120 --> 00:16:08,960
-ASHILDR: "Me"?
-Mayor Me.

350
00:16:09,040 --> 00:16:10,080
ASHILDR: Mayor is a title.

351
00:16:10,160 --> 00:16:12,720
I give myself a title
for the same reason you do, Doctor.

352
00:16:12,800 --> 00:16:13,920
Something to live up to.

353
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:15,680
DOCTOR: Difficult, isn't it?

354
00:16:15,760 --> 00:16:16,880
How long have you been here?

355
00:16:16,960 --> 00:16:18,760
ASHILDR: Since Waterloo.
DOCTOR: The battle?

356
00:16:18,840 --> 00:16:21,240
ASHILDR: No, the station.
Really, Doctor!

357
00:16:21,320 --> 00:16:23,400
Tread carefully while you're here.

358
00:16:23,480 --> 00:16:26,280
Some of your greatest enemies
are within a few feet of you.

359
00:16:26,360 --> 00:16:27,440
As far as you're concerned,

360
00:16:27,520 --> 00:16:29,640
this is the most
dangerous street in London.

361
00:16:29,720 --> 00:16:30,720
Fascinating.

362
00:16:30,800 --> 00:16:33,440
Now can we skip to the part where you
want Rigsy dead for some reason?

363
00:16:33,520 --> 00:16:35,480
WOMAN 1: It's him! He's back!

364
00:16:35,560 --> 00:16:36,960
The murderer!

365
00:16:37,040 --> 00:16:38,440
It's best we get him inside first.

366
00:16:38,520 --> 00:16:40,800
MAN 1: Murderer,
you're not welcome here.

367
00:16:40,880 --> 00:16:43,400
They look at me as if they
want to kill me themselves.

368
00:16:43,480 --> 00:16:45,000
MAN 2: We don't want
your kind around here.

369
00:16:46,120 --> 00:16:47,160
MAN 3: Murderer!

370
00:16:47,240 --> 00:16:48,240
(SNARLING)

371
00:16:49,400 --> 00:16:50,720
WOMAN 2: Murderer!

372
00:16:51,160 --> 00:16:53,280
Like I said, it's best we get inside.

373
00:16:53,560 --> 00:16:55,200
(PEOPLE YELLING INDISTINCTLY)

374
00:16:57,400 --> 00:16:58,600
WOMAN 3: Filthy murderer!

375
00:17:07,920 --> 00:17:08,920
Wait, Clara!

376
00:17:09,800 --> 00:17:10,800
Look.

377
00:17:16,960 --> 00:17:19,280
DOCTOR: This misdirection
circuit of yours is remarkable.

378
00:17:19,360 --> 00:17:20,360
(RAVEN CROWS)

379
00:17:21,480 --> 00:17:23,960
The cloaking device
that hides the street

380
00:17:24,040 --> 00:17:25,960
makes everyone look like humans.

381
00:17:26,440 --> 00:17:27,960
It's no device.

382
00:17:28,480 --> 00:17:30,080
It's the lurkworms.

383
00:17:30,760 --> 00:17:32,160
Quite something, aren't they?

384
00:17:32,680 --> 00:17:34,760
The light is a telepathic field.

385
00:17:35,880 --> 00:17:37,840
It normalises everything you see.

386
00:17:37,920 --> 00:17:40,480
Places it within the compass
of your expectations.

387
00:17:41,280 --> 00:17:42,760
Your experiences.

388
00:17:45,080 --> 00:17:47,000
You can bypass them, of course.

389
00:17:52,440 --> 00:17:53,480
(EXCLAIMS)

390
00:17:59,360 --> 00:18:01,040
Don't worry. We're perfectly safe.

391
00:18:01,920 --> 00:18:02,960
Yes.

392
00:18:03,040 --> 00:18:04,320
A phrase I find is usually followed

393
00:18:04,400 --> 00:18:07,000
by a lot of screaming
and running and bleeding.

394
00:18:08,080 --> 00:18:09,320
I brokered a truce.

395
00:18:10,360 --> 00:18:12,560
We have strict rules
against violence here.

396
00:18:12,640 --> 00:18:14,120
Rules every creature must abide by

397
00:18:14,200 --> 00:18:16,000
if they wish to remain on the street.

398
00:18:16,080 --> 00:18:17,120
MAN 1: Get away from us.

399
00:18:17,200 --> 00:18:18,440
MAN 2: Don't want your kind around here.

400
00:18:18,520 --> 00:18:20,320
ASHILDR: What's better,
that they're in here with me,

401
00:18:20,400 --> 00:18:22,080
peaceful and cooperative,

402
00:18:22,160 --> 00:18:24,440
or out there on Earth like the Zygons?

403
00:18:24,880 --> 00:18:27,440
We haven't had an act of violence
on this street for a hundred years

404
00:18:27,520 --> 00:18:29,640
until yesterday when your friend here

405
00:18:29,720 --> 00:18:32,360
attacked one of our most
vulnerable residents.

406
00:18:33,240 --> 00:18:34,960
How did Rigsy even get in?

407
00:18:36,080 --> 00:18:37,920
I mean, we barely managed it.

408
00:18:38,160 --> 00:18:39,880
And we knew what we were looking for.

409
00:18:42,480 --> 00:18:44,080
ASHILDR: She was found
at the entrance to the street.

410
00:18:46,800 --> 00:18:48,440
No weapon on the scene.

411
00:18:48,520 --> 00:18:51,160
But the cause of death
is likely the head wound.

412
00:18:51,240 --> 00:18:53,400
It seems she was knocked
to the cobblestones.

413
00:18:53,480 --> 00:18:54,480
CLARA: Seems?

414
00:18:54,560 --> 00:18:56,640
You've sentenced Rigsy to death.

415
00:18:56,720 --> 00:18:58,560
Yet you don't know
exactly what's going on.

416
00:18:58,640 --> 00:18:59,920
He was found over the body.

417
00:19:01,240 --> 00:19:04,680
My people were angry, frightened.
I had to act.

418
00:19:04,760 --> 00:19:05,840
CLARA: This is ridiculous. This is...

419
00:19:05,920 --> 00:19:06,920
What was her name?

420
00:19:07,160 --> 00:19:08,160
ASHILDR: Anna.

421
00:19:08,960 --> 00:19:11,800
We're keeping her here until someone can
take her home for burial.

422
00:19:13,400 --> 00:19:14,760
She's a Janus?

423
00:19:15,920 --> 00:19:17,840
She escaped slavery.

424
00:19:17,920 --> 00:19:19,560
She fled here with her child.

425
00:19:19,640 --> 00:19:21,560
-The child, a daughter?
-No, a boy.

426
00:19:22,760 --> 00:19:23,880
Is that bad?

427
00:19:23,960 --> 00:19:25,680
No, it's not bad. It's just unhelpful.

428
00:19:26,800 --> 00:19:28,880
A daughter might have
seen who killed her mother.

429
00:19:32,840 --> 00:19:34,760
The female Janus is psychic.

430
00:19:35,520 --> 00:19:37,760
One face sees into the future,

431
00:19:37,840 --> 00:19:39,720
the other looks behind her
into the past.

432
00:19:40,360 --> 00:19:41,920
CLARA: I think we saw her son outside.

433
00:19:42,440 --> 00:19:43,440
RIGSY: Clara.

434
00:19:44,240 --> 00:19:45,440
What if I did do it?

435
00:19:46,120 --> 00:19:48,480
I mean, I wouldn't have
meant to hurt her, but...

436
00:19:49,600 --> 00:19:51,520
What if I wandered in
and saw what she really looked like?

437
00:19:51,600 --> 00:19:52,600
What if I freaked?

438
00:19:53,520 --> 00:19:55,680
DOCTOR: You didn't just wander in here.

439
00:19:55,760 --> 00:19:57,400
You were called here at 6:00 a.m.

440
00:19:57,960 --> 00:19:59,400
By a number from a mystery phone.

441
00:19:59,480 --> 00:20:01,920
There is no way you did this.

442
00:20:02,240 --> 00:20:03,240
ASHILDR: So what then?

443
00:20:04,480 --> 00:20:06,240
You think someone
called him here? Set him up?

444
00:20:06,640 --> 00:20:08,680
Yes. Obviously.

445
00:20:08,760 --> 00:20:10,880
Which means one of your
pet aliens out there

446
00:20:10,960 --> 00:20:12,240
is the real killer.

447
00:20:12,320 --> 00:20:14,200
-(KNOCKS ON DOOR)
-MAN: I just need to talk to her.

448
00:20:14,280 --> 00:20:15,680
Excuse me, I'm sorry.

449
00:20:15,760 --> 00:20:17,920
Yes, please, go.

450
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:19,920
It's not like we've got
a ticking clock or anything.

451
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:21,640
MAN: Mayor, I'm begging you, please!

452
00:20:21,720 --> 00:20:22,920
DOCTOR: Forty-one minutes.

453
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:24,280
MAN: Lock me up.

454
00:20:24,880 --> 00:20:26,120
Throw us out.

455
00:20:26,680 --> 00:20:28,920
Anything but this. Please.

456
00:20:29,600 --> 00:20:31,400
I only took it to save her.

457
00:20:33,200 --> 00:20:34,440
How many minutes left?

458
00:20:37,240 --> 00:20:38,760
Two, Madam Mayor.

459
00:20:44,360 --> 00:20:47,440
ASHILDR: This man stole medical rations.

460
00:20:47,520 --> 00:20:49,080
He broke a rule of the street

461
00:20:49,160 --> 00:20:50,720
and he stole from all of you.

462
00:20:51,680 --> 00:20:54,440
And, yes, I can remove the Chronolock.

463
00:20:56,880 --> 00:20:57,920
But I won't.

464
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:01,440
Our rules keep us safe.

465
00:21:04,360 --> 00:21:05,360
Give it to me.

466
00:21:06,840 --> 00:21:07,840
Please.

467
00:21:08,960 --> 00:21:10,120
Tell me I can have it.

468
00:21:10,200 --> 00:21:11,560
One word, say it.

469
00:21:12,520 --> 00:21:13,520
Say yes.

470
00:21:14,280 --> 00:21:18,400
I did this to save you,
you silly old thing.

471
00:21:19,600 --> 00:21:22,080
You really think I could lose you now?

472
00:21:28,080 --> 00:21:29,360
RIGSY: What's happening?

473
00:21:31,040 --> 00:21:32,760
It's called a quantum shade.
It's kind of a spirit.

474
00:21:33,600 --> 00:21:35,520
Once it's bound to a victim,

475
00:21:35,600 --> 00:21:39,560
you can flee across
all of Time and all of the Universe,

476
00:21:39,640 --> 00:21:41,040
and it would still find you.

477
00:21:41,960 --> 00:21:42,960
(CROWS)

478
00:21:48,920 --> 00:21:49,920
(CROWS)

479
00:21:50,800 --> 00:21:52,720
Don't run, stay with her.

480
00:21:57,160 --> 00:21:58,160
(SOBS)

481
00:21:58,520 --> 00:21:59,600
Don't go.

482
00:22:00,600 --> 00:22:01,760
Why do they always run?

483
00:22:06,920 --> 00:22:08,520
(WHIMPERING)

484
00:22:11,080 --> 00:22:12,880
MAN: Help me somebody, please!

485
00:22:12,960 --> 00:22:15,200
At least give him a merciful death.

486
00:22:16,520 --> 00:22:19,640
You think a Cyberman
fears a merciful death?

487
00:22:19,720 --> 00:22:20,960
MAN: Help me! Help me! Please!

488
00:22:22,040 --> 00:22:25,320
Peace on this street
depends on one thing,

489
00:22:25,400 --> 00:22:29,160
to break it in any way
is to face the raven.

490
00:22:29,760 --> 00:22:31,160
MAN: Please, help me!

491
00:22:32,760 --> 00:22:34,040
(CROWING)

492
00:22:39,680 --> 00:22:40,840
(RAVEN CROWS)

493
00:22:42,160 --> 00:22:43,360
(SCREAMING)

494
00:22:44,880 --> 00:22:46,080
(WOMAN GASPS)

495
00:22:55,840 --> 00:22:57,040
(WOMAN SOBS)

496
00:23:08,760 --> 00:23:09,760
(CROWING)

497
00:23:19,320 --> 00:23:22,400
I have no wish to harm your
friend if he is innocent, Doctor.

498
00:23:24,360 --> 00:23:25,640
Question anyone.

499
00:23:26,720 --> 00:23:28,480
Examine the body.

500
00:23:28,560 --> 00:23:31,280
But it's not me you need to
convince of Rigsy's innocence.

501
00:23:32,760 --> 00:23:33,960
It's them.

502
00:23:45,520 --> 00:23:48,080
Okay, we split up, cover more ground.

503
00:23:48,560 --> 00:23:49,720
I'm good cop, you're bad cop.

504
00:23:49,800 --> 00:23:51,080
No, no, no, we don't have to...

505
00:23:51,160 --> 00:23:52,440
Can I not be the good cop?

506
00:23:52,520 --> 00:23:54,520
Doctor, we've discussed this.
Your face...

507
00:23:54,600 --> 00:23:57,400
Oh, yeah.
Well, forget about cops, right.

508
00:23:57,480 --> 00:23:58,720
Forget about finding the real killer.

509
00:23:58,800 --> 00:23:59,840
You heard Ashildr.

510
00:23:59,920 --> 00:24:01,840
All we have to do
is persuade these creatures

511
00:24:01,920 --> 00:24:03,520
that it isn't Rigsy.

512
00:24:03,600 --> 00:24:04,640
And fast!

513
00:24:04,720 --> 00:24:06,640
(RIGSY SHUSHING)

514
00:24:06,720 --> 00:24:08,320
Shh, baby girl, shh.

515
00:24:08,400 --> 00:24:09,840
JEN: She's been like this all day.

516
00:24:09,920 --> 00:24:12,320
Now, listen, you be good
for your mum for me, okay?

517
00:24:13,440 --> 00:24:15,040
And I'm doing my best
to get home to you guys.

518
00:24:15,120 --> 00:24:17,160
-She won't stop crying.
-RIGSY: Yeah. I know.

519
00:24:17,840 --> 00:24:19,360
Yeah, she can probably
tell you're upset.

520
00:24:21,240 --> 00:24:22,320
CLARA: Rump.

521
00:24:23,920 --> 00:24:25,720
It's, um, Rump, isn't it?

522
00:24:27,320 --> 00:24:29,280
That man's wife, she said something.

523
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:31,680
"Give it to me, tell me I can have it."

524
00:24:31,760 --> 00:24:32,800
What did she mean?

525
00:24:33,760 --> 00:24:36,080
Two ways to survive a quantum shade.

526
00:24:37,040 --> 00:24:39,120
The shade's master
removes the Chronolock...

527
00:24:40,840 --> 00:24:42,680
Or you can give it to someone else.

528
00:24:43,520 --> 00:24:44,760
Give it? You can just...

529
00:24:44,840 --> 00:24:46,040
No, you can't just push it on someone,

530
00:24:46,120 --> 00:24:47,920
it's not that simple.

531
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:50,040
It must be taken willingly.

532
00:24:50,120 --> 00:24:51,920
The death's already locked in.

533
00:24:52,960 --> 00:24:54,520
You can pass it on, but...

534
00:24:55,640 --> 00:24:57,080
You can't cheat it.

535
00:25:15,400 --> 00:25:17,160
RIGSY: You're serious?

536
00:25:17,240 --> 00:25:19,040
You actually expect me
to give you my death sentence?

537
00:25:19,120 --> 00:25:20,960
Shh! Go on.

538
00:25:21,680 --> 00:25:24,360
I've always wanted a tattoo.
You know, something small, discreet.

539
00:25:24,440 --> 00:25:25,880
Clara, cut it out.

540
00:25:25,960 --> 00:25:27,320
Look, weren't you listening?

541
00:25:27,400 --> 00:25:29,360
I'm under the Mayor's
personal protection,

542
00:25:29,440 --> 00:25:31,520
and it's absolute, apparently.

543
00:25:31,600 --> 00:25:32,840
Look, she controls the Raven.

544
00:25:32,920 --> 00:25:34,920
So I will never have to face it.
This is clever.

545
00:25:35,000 --> 00:25:36,800
But this is putting you in danger.

546
00:25:36,880 --> 00:25:39,560
No, this is us talking the
opposition into their own trap.

547
00:25:39,640 --> 00:25:41,800
This is Doctor 101. We're buying time.

548
00:25:41,880 --> 00:25:43,320
We get all of the aliens on our side,

549
00:25:43,400 --> 00:25:44,640
in the next half an hour...

550
00:25:44,720 --> 00:25:46,880
And then, we reveal
I've got the Chronolock, not you...

551
00:25:46,960 --> 00:25:48,400
And boom!

552
00:25:48,480 --> 00:25:50,120
We buy ourselves more time
to find the real killer.

553
00:25:50,200 --> 00:25:51,560
The Doctor would never let you do this.

554
00:25:51,640 --> 00:25:55,160
Doctor 102. Never tell anyone
your actual plan.

555
00:25:55,240 --> 00:25:56,600
He'll have a tantrum when he finds out.

556
00:25:56,680 --> 00:25:58,800
And then, when we confront Ashildr,

557
00:25:59,720 --> 00:26:01,960
she'll want to take
the Chronolock off just to shut him up.

558
00:26:04,960 --> 00:26:08,480
What happens if you don't go home
tonight, to Jen and Lucy, hey?

559
00:26:08,560 --> 00:26:10,880
If you never go home?

560
00:26:10,960 --> 00:26:12,880
You really want your little girl
growing up without a father

561
00:26:12,960 --> 00:26:15,080
just because he wouldn't take a risk?

562
00:26:17,160 --> 00:26:18,600
You trusted us to save you...

563
00:26:18,680 --> 00:26:20,400
So trust us, come on!

564
00:26:25,920 --> 00:26:27,600
Okay. All right.

565
00:26:28,960 --> 00:26:30,360
All right, how do we do this, then?

566
00:26:30,440 --> 00:26:33,200
Well, I was kind of hoping
that would be it.

567
00:26:33,280 --> 00:26:35,920
I say I want it, you say can
have it, you know, done deal.

568
00:26:36,000 --> 00:26:37,720
-(CHUCKLES)
-Hey, turn around, let me see.

569
00:26:48,160 --> 00:26:49,440
(GASPS)

570
00:26:51,080 --> 00:26:52,760
(CROWING)

571
00:26:56,160 --> 00:26:57,240
(RIGSY CHUCKLES)

572
00:26:57,840 --> 00:26:59,160
So, this your life then?

573
00:26:59,240 --> 00:27:01,840
Just bouncing around time
saving people, right?

574
00:27:01,920 --> 00:27:03,520
No, not every day.

575
00:27:03,600 --> 00:27:05,320
(CHUCKLES) You know, sometimes,

576
00:27:05,400 --> 00:27:07,320
Jane Austen and I prank each other.

577
00:27:07,400 --> 00:27:09,280
Oh, she is the worst. I love her.

578
00:27:09,360 --> 00:27:10,480
(SIGHS)

579
00:27:10,560 --> 00:27:11,760
Take that how you like.

580
00:27:13,680 --> 00:27:15,320
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

581
00:27:15,400 --> 00:27:17,560
DOCTOR: Are you sure it wasn't
someone from the street?

582
00:27:17,640 --> 00:27:19,960
I told you already, there wasn't
anyone up that end of the street

583
00:27:20,040 --> 00:27:21,760
except Anna and the human.

584
00:27:21,840 --> 00:27:25,480
I've identified 27 different
species on the street so far.

585
00:27:25,560 --> 00:27:27,880
Fifteen of whom
are known for aggression.

586
00:27:28,800 --> 00:27:31,400
Why is it so hard to believe
that one of them is capable of murder?

587
00:27:31,480 --> 00:27:33,480
Capable of murder, yeah.

588
00:27:33,560 --> 00:27:34,680
Capable of killing Anna...

589
00:27:34,760 --> 00:27:35,800
No.

590
00:27:35,880 --> 00:27:37,600
Why not? What's so special about her?

591
00:27:38,320 --> 00:27:39,960
It was the way she looked at you.

592
00:27:40,040 --> 00:27:41,640
Like she understood.

593
00:27:41,720 --> 00:27:44,480
One glance into your past
and she felt it all.

594
00:27:45,240 --> 00:27:47,680
Every battle, every loss.

595
00:27:47,760 --> 00:27:49,480
So you just want the human
dead, is that it?

596
00:27:49,560 --> 00:27:50,920
You don't get it, do you?

597
00:27:51,000 --> 00:27:53,040
If the human didn't do it
that means one of us did it.

598
00:27:53,120 --> 00:27:56,000
Which means folks start pointing
fingers, turning on each other.

599
00:27:56,080 --> 00:27:58,160
And once we turn
on each other in here, that's it.

600
00:27:58,240 --> 00:27:59,920
I might as well be back in a war zone.

601
00:28:00,000 --> 00:28:01,440
So you'll just let Rigsy die?

602
00:28:01,520 --> 00:28:03,320
To keep the peace? Yeah, I will.

603
00:28:04,080 --> 00:28:06,200
Your friend, acting like
he was all scared of us,

604
00:28:06,280 --> 00:28:07,560
calling for a doctor.

605
00:28:09,080 --> 00:28:10,200
-A what?
-I know.

606
00:28:10,280 --> 00:28:11,920
The cheek of him.

607
00:28:12,000 --> 00:28:14,600
Humans can survive losing entire limbs

608
00:28:14,680 --> 00:28:15,840
and I'm supposed to believe that he...

609
00:28:15,920 --> 00:28:17,040
Shut up! Shut up!

610
00:28:17,120 --> 00:28:18,320
The other thing he said,
the second thing...

611
00:28:18,400 --> 00:28:20,440
(STUTTERING)
You said he was scared and...

612
00:28:20,520 --> 00:28:22,720
And he asked the Mayor
to call him a doctor.

613
00:28:23,720 --> 00:28:25,920
-Poor Anna, dead at his feet...
-Shh.

614
00:28:27,440 --> 00:28:29,480
Did he say a doctor or the Doctor?

615
00:28:29,560 --> 00:28:30,880
This is very, very important.

616
00:28:30,960 --> 00:28:32,200
The Doctor.

617
00:28:32,280 --> 00:28:33,880
There was nothing wrong with him, mind.

618
00:28:33,960 --> 00:28:36,320
It was all just your
standard human lies.

619
00:28:42,120 --> 00:28:45,080
Clara gave you my number
for emergencies.

620
00:28:45,160 --> 00:28:47,280
So when you wake up with
a weird tattoo on your neck

621
00:28:47,360 --> 00:28:48,640
and no memory of the last 24 hours,

622
00:28:48,720 --> 00:28:50,480
the first thing you do
is call the Doctor.

623
00:28:51,520 --> 00:28:53,120
Call the Doctor?

624
00:28:53,200 --> 00:28:55,040
But you find yourself accused of murder

625
00:28:55,120 --> 00:28:57,240
on a strange alien street
in the middle of London...

626
00:28:57,320 --> 00:28:58,840
Only they've taken your phone,

627
00:28:58,920 --> 00:29:01,760
so you beg the woman in charge
to call me instead.

628
00:29:01,840 --> 00:29:03,840
She knew you and I were friends.

629
00:29:04,680 --> 00:29:06,320
So why'd she lie?

630
00:29:06,400 --> 00:29:07,640
Unless she had something to hide.

631
00:29:07,720 --> 00:29:08,760
ALIEN: Murderer!

632
00:29:10,240 --> 00:29:12,000
DOCTOR: There's something
very wrong here.

633
00:29:12,080 --> 00:29:13,720
And we're running out of time.

634
00:29:13,800 --> 00:29:15,720
(CLEARS THROAT) There's 12 minutes left.

635
00:29:15,800 --> 00:29:17,120
I'm not giving up yet.

636
00:29:17,200 --> 00:29:18,320
Look, Clara.

637
00:29:18,400 --> 00:29:20,120
Even if one of them knows something,

638
00:29:20,240 --> 00:29:22,080
they're not gonna come forward.

639
00:29:22,160 --> 00:29:23,240
The way they look at me.

640
00:29:24,640 --> 00:29:26,520
The way they look at you?

641
00:29:26,600 --> 00:29:27,840
RIGSY: What?

642
00:29:29,200 --> 00:29:30,240
(KNOCKING)

643
00:29:33,440 --> 00:29:34,920
CLARA: (WHISPERING) Hey, wait!

644
00:29:37,120 --> 00:29:38,920
Everyone here is weird around us,

645
00:29:39,000 --> 00:29:40,800
because of Rigsy, but not you.

646
00:29:42,600 --> 00:29:45,520
You look at me and the Doctor
like you're confused.

647
00:29:45,600 --> 00:29:46,600
Like you're curious.

648
00:29:47,160 --> 00:29:49,120
-I don't know what you mean.
-You do.

649
00:29:49,720 --> 00:29:51,360
You know Rigsy is innocent

650
00:29:51,440 --> 00:29:54,280
because you can
look into his past and you can see it.

651
00:29:55,320 --> 00:29:56,600
CLARA: Can't you?

652
00:30:01,920 --> 00:30:04,200
She dressed you as a boy to protect you.

653
00:30:04,280 --> 00:30:06,880
But, really, you're a girl.

654
00:30:08,560 --> 00:30:09,720
You have the gift.

655
00:30:10,440 --> 00:30:11,880
It is no gift.

656
00:30:12,440 --> 00:30:14,080
I'm safe as a boy.

657
00:30:15,440 --> 00:30:17,440
This is the first place
I have ever been safe

658
00:30:17,520 --> 00:30:20,240
and you want me to throw it away?

659
00:30:20,320 --> 00:30:21,560
To admit what I am?

660
00:30:21,640 --> 00:30:24,400
The Mayor, what is she up to?

661
00:30:25,400 --> 00:30:26,800
It's nothing good, is it?

662
00:30:27,880 --> 00:30:29,480
I can't see everything.

663
00:30:31,640 --> 00:30:33,960
But she thinks
she's doing the right thing.

664
00:30:34,040 --> 00:30:35,640
They usually do.

665
00:30:36,760 --> 00:30:38,400
If what Ashildr is doing is harmless,

666
00:30:38,480 --> 00:30:40,720
then we will just walk out of that door.

667
00:30:40,800 --> 00:30:42,480
No one will know of your abilities.

668
00:30:43,400 --> 00:30:46,360
-But if it's not...
-I don't know what she means to do.

669
00:30:47,360 --> 00:30:50,280
Now, I'm trying but I can't see it.

670
00:30:50,360 --> 00:30:52,680
I can't see it because it involves you.

671
00:30:53,800 --> 00:30:57,920
When I look at you,
I can't tell your past from your future

672
00:30:58,000 --> 00:31:00,160
and there's so very much of both.

673
00:31:01,720 --> 00:31:04,880
This isn't about Rigsy. It's about me!

674
00:31:13,680 --> 00:31:15,960
She couldn't just ask you here.

675
00:31:17,760 --> 00:31:19,360
She needed a mystery.

676
00:31:20,160 --> 00:31:23,000
You can never resist a mystery.

677
00:31:23,800 --> 00:31:26,160
-She's afraid.
-Afraid of what?

678
00:31:27,120 --> 00:31:28,200
Of whom?

679
00:31:29,440 --> 00:31:30,680
I can't see.

680
00:31:38,280 --> 00:31:39,600
I'm sorry.

681
00:31:45,520 --> 00:31:46,640
(CROWS)

682
00:31:46,720 --> 00:31:48,480
You hold your tongue,
we've got 10 minutes left!

683
00:31:48,560 --> 00:31:50,080
(CONTINUES CROWING)

684
00:31:51,760 --> 00:31:54,160
Ashildr said Anna was being
taken home for burial.

685
00:31:55,000 --> 00:31:57,160
But the Janus burn their dead.

686
00:31:57,240 --> 00:31:58,560
RIGSY: Is that true?

687
00:32:00,400 --> 00:32:03,880
So, look, Ashildr got it wrong.
What does it matter?

688
00:32:03,960 --> 00:32:05,520
-Come on!
-There's something about this text.

689
00:32:05,600 --> 00:32:06,960
Look, Doctor, we don't have time.

690
00:32:09,120 --> 00:32:12,000
-What is it?
-DOCTOR: It looks like medical data.

691
00:32:12,800 --> 00:32:16,160
But it can't be, she's dead.
She isn't breathing.

692
00:32:17,400 --> 00:32:19,480
This thing is a stasis pod.

693
00:32:19,560 --> 00:32:20,560
If you're dead,

694
00:32:20,640 --> 00:32:22,280
it's a kind of fancy refrigerator.

695
00:32:23,120 --> 00:32:25,320
-But if you're alive...
-(POD WHIRRING)

696
00:32:25,400 --> 00:32:27,680
(SOFTLY) It simply keeps you that way.

697
00:32:27,760 --> 00:32:30,080
She's alive?

698
00:32:30,160 --> 00:32:31,680
-She's alive.
-Well, get her out...

699
00:32:31,760 --> 00:32:32,880
Get her out of there!

700
00:32:33,280 --> 00:32:34,840
There must be a way to unlock it.

701
00:32:34,920 --> 00:32:35,960
Something basic, something simple...

702
00:32:36,040 --> 00:32:37,080
A keyhole!

703
00:32:37,360 --> 00:32:39,240
A keyhole would be very handy, yes.
But I haven't got...

704
00:32:39,320 --> 00:32:41,560
No, no, no, no! A keyhole. Look!

705
00:32:41,640 --> 00:32:44,360
-Look.
-I'll find her. I'll get the key.

706
00:32:44,440 --> 00:32:46,000
No, Anahson, stay here.

707
00:32:47,960 --> 00:32:50,680
There's a reason
that the Mayor has gone AWOL.

708
00:32:51,960 --> 00:32:54,520
She means for us to release your mother.

709
00:32:54,600 --> 00:32:57,320
But she doesn't want us to use her key.

710
00:32:57,400 --> 00:32:58,600
She wants to use mine.

711
00:32:58,680 --> 00:33:00,720
The Tardis.
That's what this is all about?

712
00:33:04,440 --> 00:33:05,600
Doctor, wait!

713
00:33:05,680 --> 00:33:07,040
DOCTOR: This girl needs her mother.

714
00:33:07,120 --> 00:33:08,120
-(LOCK CLICKS)
-(GASPS)

715
00:33:08,200 --> 00:33:09,480
-Doctor!
-(DOCTOR MUTTERING)

716
00:33:09,560 --> 00:33:11,280
-(GROANS)
-What's it doing?

717
00:33:11,360 --> 00:33:12,680
(CLATTERING)

718
00:33:15,600 --> 00:33:17,120
(GASPING)

719
00:33:19,240 --> 00:33:21,240
Mum!

720
00:33:21,320 --> 00:33:23,040
ANAHSON: Mum, are you okay?

721
00:33:23,120 --> 00:33:25,680
ASHILDR: She'll be perfectly
fine in a few moments.

722
00:33:25,760 --> 00:33:27,600
I assure you.

723
00:33:27,680 --> 00:33:29,520
There are easier ways
to steal a key, you know?

724
00:33:29,600 --> 00:33:33,120
I don't want your Tardis.
That's not what this is about.

725
00:33:34,840 --> 00:33:36,800
Rigsy, come here,
I'll remove your Chronolock.

726
00:33:36,880 --> 00:33:37,920
What is this, Ashildr?

727
00:33:38,000 --> 00:33:39,360
You can't possibly think
this is gonna keep me here?

728
00:33:39,440 --> 00:33:40,760
It's not a restraint.

729
00:33:42,480 --> 00:33:44,400
-It's a teleport bracelet.
-What?

730
00:33:44,480 --> 00:33:46,520
I'll give you time
to say goodbye, don't worry.

731
00:33:46,880 --> 00:33:48,160
No one will be hurt.

732
00:33:48,240 --> 00:33:49,920
Where are you sending me?

733
00:33:51,200 --> 00:33:53,080
I made a deal to protect this street.

734
00:33:54,400 --> 00:33:57,520
They take you,
I take the keys, you can't be traced.

735
00:33:57,600 --> 00:33:59,240
I do as they tell me
and the street is safe.

736
00:34:00,000 --> 00:34:02,600
"They"? Who are they?

737
00:34:02,680 --> 00:34:04,120
One more thing...

738
00:34:06,080 --> 00:34:07,480
Your confession dial.

739
00:34:10,200 --> 00:34:12,040
They have other means of procuring it

740
00:34:12,120 --> 00:34:14,560
but I understand it's likely
to be on your person.

741
00:34:16,560 --> 00:34:19,400
Please, no resistance.

742
00:34:20,360 --> 00:34:21,880
You've already lost.

743
00:34:27,640 --> 00:34:28,800
What is it?

744
00:34:28,880 --> 00:34:30,960
In your terms,
my last will and testament.

745
00:34:31,040 --> 00:34:32,400
How does it work?

746
00:34:32,480 --> 00:34:34,040
I've no idea.

747
00:34:35,520 --> 00:34:37,280
Well, thank you, anyway.

748
00:34:38,520 --> 00:34:40,080
ASHILDR: Rigsy, your neck.

749
00:34:41,160 --> 00:34:43,480
Clara, what are you playing at?
The Chronolock?

750
00:34:45,880 --> 00:34:47,640
Take the teleport off him first.

751
00:34:48,800 --> 00:34:50,680
Look, I don't have it,
I'm telling you. Clara does.

752
00:34:55,440 --> 00:34:56,440
No.

753
00:34:57,560 --> 00:34:58,680
No, you didn't.

754
00:35:00,120 --> 00:35:02,360
Go on, then. Take it off.

755
00:35:02,480 --> 00:35:03,920
Clara, you didn't!

756
00:35:06,000 --> 00:35:07,160
(GASPS)

757
00:35:08,200 --> 00:35:11,120
I had no idea
she'd do something so stupid.

758
00:35:11,200 --> 00:35:12,960
(GASPING)

759
00:35:13,040 --> 00:35:14,600
I swear!

760
00:35:14,680 --> 00:35:16,480
I never meant for anyone to get hurt.

761
00:35:17,800 --> 00:35:19,480
Look, what were you thinking?

762
00:35:20,280 --> 00:35:21,440
Sacrificing yourself...

763
00:35:21,520 --> 00:35:23,240
I wasn't sacrificing anything.

764
00:35:23,320 --> 00:35:26,200
Strategy. Back-up plan
to buy us more time.

765
00:35:26,280 --> 00:35:28,040
Who told you to go to her?

766
00:35:28,120 --> 00:35:29,120
Nobody did. I did. Rump said.

767
00:35:29,200 --> 00:35:30,680
What exactly did Rump say?

768
00:35:30,760 --> 00:35:31,760
He said that death is locked in.

769
00:35:31,840 --> 00:35:34,320
You can pass it on but you...

770
00:35:34,400 --> 00:35:35,520
(SOFTLY) But what?

771
00:35:38,920 --> 00:35:40,160
But...

772
00:35:40,240 --> 00:35:42,080
ASHILDR: But you can't
cheat it altogether.

773
00:35:48,200 --> 00:35:49,920
(CROWING)

774
00:35:52,960 --> 00:35:55,080
Clara, you didn't tell me that.

775
00:35:56,400 --> 00:35:57,440
Give it back to me, now!

776
00:35:57,520 --> 00:35:58,840
She can't.

777
00:36:02,240 --> 00:36:03,520
Clara, I made a contract with the shade

778
00:36:03,600 --> 00:36:05,080
when I put the Chronolock on Rigsy.

779
00:36:07,360 --> 00:36:09,320
I promised it a soul
and only I can break that contract.

780
00:36:09,400 --> 00:36:12,480
When you took it from him,
you changed the terms.

781
00:36:13,920 --> 00:36:15,320
You cut me out of the deal.

782
00:36:18,360 --> 00:36:19,680
(CROWING)

783
00:36:31,440 --> 00:36:33,040
We can fix this, can't we?

784
00:36:38,320 --> 00:36:39,720
We always fix it.

785
00:36:42,400 --> 00:36:43,520
No.

786
00:36:50,040 --> 00:36:52,880
But you can. Fix this, fix it now!

787
00:36:54,000 --> 00:36:56,600
It... It's not possible. I... I can't.

788
00:36:56,680 --> 00:36:57,880
Yes, it is. You can.

789
00:36:57,960 --> 00:37:00,560
And you will,
or this street will be over.

790
00:37:00,640 --> 00:37:02,560
I'll show you and all your
funny little friends

791
00:37:02,640 --> 00:37:04,240
to the whole laughing world.

792
00:37:04,320 --> 00:37:06,320
I'll bring UNIT, I'll bring Zygons.

793
00:37:06,400 --> 00:37:08,880
Give a minute,
I'll bring the Daleks and the Cybermen.

794
00:37:08,960 --> 00:37:10,800
You will save Clara.

795
00:37:10,880 --> 00:37:12,360
And you will do it now.

796
00:37:12,440 --> 00:37:15,000
Or I will rain hell on you
for the rest of time.

797
00:37:15,080 --> 00:37:16,200
Doctor, stop talking like that.

798
00:37:16,280 --> 00:37:17,320
You can't.

799
00:37:17,400 --> 00:37:19,240
I can do whatever the hell I like.

800
00:37:19,320 --> 00:37:21,440
You've read the stories.
You know who I am.

801
00:37:22,680 --> 00:37:23,880
And in all that time,

802
00:37:23,960 --> 00:37:26,640
did you ever hear anything
about anyone who stopped me?

803
00:37:27,760 --> 00:37:30,040
I know the Doctor. The Doctor...

804
00:37:30,120 --> 00:37:33,640
The Doctor is no longer here.
You are stuck with me.

805
00:37:33,720 --> 00:37:35,880
And I will end you
and everything you love.

806
00:37:36,560 --> 00:37:38,800
Doctor, for God's sake will you stop?

807
00:37:38,880 --> 00:37:41,000
-Now!
-I did this.

808
00:37:41,080 --> 00:37:43,560
Do you hear me?
I did this. This is my fault.

809
00:37:43,640 --> 00:37:45,200
-I don't care!
-Liar.

810
00:37:45,280 --> 00:37:47,440
You always care. Always have.

811
00:37:49,120 --> 00:37:50,720
Your reign of terror will end
with the sight of the first

812
00:37:50,800 --> 00:37:52,080
crying child and you know it.

813
00:37:52,160 --> 00:37:53,360
(SOFTLY) No, I don't.

814
00:37:56,440 --> 00:37:57,720
I do.

815
00:38:06,240 --> 00:38:07,800
Listen,

816
00:38:07,880 --> 00:38:11,000
if this is the last
I ever see of you, please...

817
00:38:12,880 --> 00:38:14,120
Not like this.

818
00:38:19,800 --> 00:38:21,320
(RAVEN CROWING)

819
00:38:26,720 --> 00:38:28,080
Is there anything you can do?

820
00:38:29,440 --> 00:38:31,480
Sorry.

821
00:38:31,560 --> 00:38:33,480
I'm truly sorry. I...

822
00:38:33,560 --> 00:38:35,360
Time's short. Yes or no?

823
00:38:36,320 --> 00:38:37,480
(SOFTLY) No.

824
00:38:51,720 --> 00:38:52,720
Well, if Danny Pink can do it, so can I.

825
00:38:52,800 --> 00:38:53,840
Do what?

826
00:38:53,920 --> 00:38:56,320
Die right, die like I mean it.
Face the Raven.

827
00:38:56,400 --> 00:38:58,080
No, this... This is...
This can't be happening.

828
00:38:58,160 --> 00:38:59,760
Maybe this is what I wanted.

829
00:38:59,840 --> 00:39:01,160
Maybe this is it.

830
00:39:01,240 --> 00:39:02,760
Maybe this is why I kept running.

831
00:39:02,880 --> 00:39:04,800
Maybe this is why
I kept taking all those stupid risks.

832
00:39:04,880 --> 00:39:05,920
Kept pushing it.

833
00:39:06,000 --> 00:39:07,000
This is my fault.

834
00:39:07,080 --> 00:39:09,440
-This is my choice.
-I let you get reckless.

835
00:39:09,520 --> 00:39:10,760
Why... Why shouldn't I be so reckless?

836
00:39:10,840 --> 00:39:13,120
You're reckless all the bloody time.

837
00:39:13,200 --> 00:39:14,440
Why can't I be like you?

838
00:39:14,520 --> 00:39:15,960
Clara, there's nothing special about me.

839
00:39:16,040 --> 00:39:17,560
I am nothing, but I am less
breakable than you.

840
00:39:17,640 --> 00:39:19,040
I should've taken care of you.

841
00:39:19,120 --> 00:39:21,840
-I never asked you to.
-You shouldn't have to ask.

842
00:39:21,920 --> 00:39:23,600
-(CROWING)
-(CROWD GASPING)

843
00:39:24,640 --> 00:39:26,600
-Clara, if I'd known...
-Don't! Shut up!

844
00:39:27,040 --> 00:39:29,760
-But, I...
-Really, Rigsy, shut up!

845
00:39:29,840 --> 00:39:32,320
If you feel guilty about this
even for one minute...

846
00:39:32,400 --> 00:39:33,600
(RAVEN CROWING)

847
00:39:43,000 --> 00:39:44,280
You...

848
00:39:47,080 --> 00:39:48,440
Now, you listen to me,

849
00:39:51,080 --> 00:39:53,120
you're gonna be alone now.

850
00:39:53,200 --> 00:39:54,440
And you're very bad at that.

851
00:39:55,080 --> 00:39:57,440
You're gonna be furious,
and you're gonna be sad.

852
00:39:57,520 --> 00:39:58,880
But listen to me,

853
00:39:58,960 --> 00:40:00,440
-don't let this change you.
-(MUTTERS)

854
00:40:00,520 --> 00:40:03,120
No, listen, whatever happens next...

855
00:40:04,440 --> 00:40:06,640
Wherever she is sending you...

856
00:40:06,720 --> 00:40:08,280
I know what you're capable of.

857
00:40:09,840 --> 00:40:12,320
You don't be a warrior.

858
00:40:12,400 --> 00:40:13,920
Promise me.

859
00:40:14,760 --> 00:40:16,000
Be a Doctor.

860
00:40:17,640 --> 00:40:19,760
What's the point of being
a Doctor if I can't cure...

861
00:40:19,840 --> 00:40:21,720
-Heal yourself.
-(EXHALES)

862
00:40:21,800 --> 00:40:23,160
You have to.

863
00:40:23,240 --> 00:40:25,560
You can't let this
turn you into a monster. So...

864
00:40:27,400 --> 00:40:29,120
I'm not asking you for a promise,

865
00:40:29,200 --> 00:40:30,640
I'm giving you an order.

866
00:40:33,600 --> 00:40:35,360
You will not insult my memory.

867
00:40:35,440 --> 00:40:37,040
There will be no revenge.

868
00:40:37,120 --> 00:40:38,240
I will die,

869
00:40:38,320 --> 00:40:41,360
and no one else here
or anywhere will suffer.

870
00:40:45,440 --> 00:40:46,600
What about me?

871
00:40:48,560 --> 00:40:50,720
If there was something I could
do about that, I would.

872
00:40:52,920 --> 00:40:54,800
I guess we're both just
gonna have to be brave.

873
00:40:59,960 --> 00:41:01,600
-Clara...
-(SIGHS)

874
00:41:04,280 --> 00:41:05,400
(EXHALES)

875
00:41:06,960 --> 00:41:09,040
Everything you're about to say,

876
00:41:09,120 --> 00:41:10,360
I already know.

877
00:41:11,840 --> 00:41:13,080
Don't do it now.

878
00:41:14,120 --> 00:41:15,600
We've already had enough bad timing.

879
00:41:17,280 --> 00:41:18,640
(RAVEN CROWS)

880
00:41:23,160 --> 00:41:24,680
Don't run.

881
00:41:28,240 --> 00:41:29,480
Stay with me.

882
00:41:30,320 --> 00:41:31,640
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

883
00:41:32,600 --> 00:41:33,840
Nah.

884
00:41:35,800 --> 00:41:37,000
You stay here.

885
00:41:38,440 --> 00:41:40,240
In the end, everyone does this alone.

886
00:41:41,080 --> 00:41:43,280
-Clara...
-This is as brave

887
00:41:44,720 --> 00:41:46,240
as I know how to be.

888
00:41:47,080 --> 00:41:48,440
(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)

889
00:41:50,040 --> 00:41:52,480
I know it's gonna hurt you
but, please...

890
00:41:54,400 --> 00:41:55,880
Be a little proud of me.

891
00:41:57,440 --> 00:41:58,640
(SIGHS)

892
00:42:11,440 --> 00:42:12,920
Goodbye, Doctor.

893
00:42:14,480 --> 00:42:15,960
(RAVEN CROWING)

894
00:42:17,240 --> 00:42:18,440
(SIGHS)

895
00:42:36,200 --> 00:42:37,680
(CROWS)

896
00:42:59,400 --> 00:43:00,760
(WHISPERS) Let me be brave.

897
00:43:02,160 --> 00:43:03,520
Let me be brave.

898
00:43:05,120 --> 00:43:06,400
(CROWING)

899
00:43:07,720 --> 00:43:09,080
(INAUDIBLY) Let me be brave.

900
00:43:10,480 --> 00:43:11,840
(GASPS)

901
00:43:20,520 --> 00:43:22,360
(INAUDIBLE SCREAMING)

902
00:43:39,560 --> 00:43:41,000
(GASPS)

903
00:44:29,560 --> 00:44:31,080
ASHILDR: I'm sorry, Doctor.

904
00:44:32,880 --> 00:44:34,240
I truly am.

905
00:44:40,960 --> 00:44:42,160
(BEEPING)

906
00:44:48,800 --> 00:44:51,600
What Clara said,
about not taking revenge,

907
00:44:51,680 --> 00:44:53,160
do you know why she said that?

908
00:44:54,360 --> 00:44:55,680
She was saving you.

909
00:44:55,800 --> 00:44:57,440
I was lost a long time ago,

910
00:44:57,520 --> 00:44:59,000
she was saving you.

911
00:45:03,040 --> 00:45:04,360
I'll do my best.

912
00:45:05,440 --> 00:45:08,120
But I strongly advise you
to keep out of my way.

913
00:45:10,520 --> 00:45:13,920
You'll find that it's a very small
universe when I'm angry with you.

914
00:45:20,320 --> 00:45:21,560
(BRACELET BEEPS)

915
00:45:32,160 --> 00:45:33,440
(WHOOSHING)

916
00:45:43,720 --> 00:45:45,720
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

917
00:46:29,960 --> 00:46:31,720
DOCTOR: This whole place
is designed to terrify me.

918
00:46:33,120 --> 00:46:34,880
(WHISPERS) I know you.

919
00:46:34,960 --> 00:46:37,040
I've seen you before.

920
00:46:37,120 --> 00:46:39,920
If you were any part
of killing her and you're not afraid,

921
00:46:40,000 --> 00:46:41,800
then you understand nothing at all.

922
00:46:42,560 --> 00:46:44,320
I am the Doctor.

923
00:46:44,400 --> 00:46:47,920
I'm coming to find you
and I will never, ever stop.

